// csr197skie.tra — component 197 new dialogue (Ducal Palace, Skie talk-to-join)
// ALL LINES SIGNED OFF AS-IS by the user 2026-07-13 (BG1/BG2 register, issue #2 / PT-4).
// Context: post-council great hall. Entar died in BG1 ch.7 and stays dead
// (comp185) — Skie may not blame Caelar for his death.

// Skie — opener (replaces the vanilla "talking to Daddy" meeting)
@0 = ~You remember me, <CHARNAME>? Skie Silvershield. They buried my father while the whole city argued about this crusade. Everyone says I should sit in his empty house and mourn. I won't.~

// Player replies to the opener
@1 = ~I am sorry for your loss, Skie. Duke Silvershield was a pillar of this city.~
@2 = ~The dukes' council is no place for mourning, Skie. Why are you here?~

// Skie — the ask
@3 = ~Because you're here. You're going after Caelar—everyone says so. Take me with you. I can open a lock and walk without a sound, and anything is better than sitting alone in Daddy's empty house.~

// Player — accept / decline
@4 = ~Very well, Skie. Gather your gear—we march north soon.~
@5 = ~No. A war camp is no place for you. Stay in Baldur's Gate.~

// Skie — join / stay behind
@6 = ~You mean it? You won't regret this, <CHARNAME>. Let's be off before the dukes think better of it.~
@7 = ~Fine. FINE. Everyone decides what's best for Skie... I'll be here. Should you change your mind.~

// Skie — re-offer if the player comes back to her in the hall
@8 = ~Changed your mind, <CHARNAME>? Good. Take me with you—the offer stands.~
@9 = ~All right, Skie. Come along.~
@10 = ~Not yet, Skie.~
